In [13]:
from sklearn.utils import resample
# Separate majority and minority classes
data_majority = data[data.chd==0]
data_minority = data[data.chd==1]
 
# Upsample minority class
data_minority_upsampled = resample(data_minority, 
                                 replace=True,     # sample with replacement
                                 n_samples=295,    # to match majority class
                                 random_state=4) # reproducible results
 
# Combine majority class with upsampled minority class
data_sampled = pd.concat([data_majority, data_minority_upsampled])
 
# Display new class counts
#data_upsampled.balance.value_counts()
data_sampled['chd'].value_counts()

fig = plt.gcf();
fig.set_size_inches(12, 10)
R=round(data_sampled.corr(method='pearson'),ndigits=3)
sns.heatmap(round(R,ndigits=2),annot=True)
plt.show()

The observation of the coefficients of the correlation matrix above suggests that:

  • Age is correlated with tobacco consumption and level of adiposity;
  • Obesity is strongly correlated with adiposity;
  • Idl is correlated with adiposity.
  • In short, older and obese subjects tend to have more fat accumulated under the skin.

from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier,AdaBoostClassifier
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, accuracy_score,confusion_matrix
from sklearn.neural_network import MLPClassifier

names = [ 
         "Decision Tree", "Random Forest", "AdaBoost","SVM RBF" ,"Neural Net"]

classifiers = [
  
    DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='gini', max_depth=5, max_features='auto'),
    RandomForestClassifier(criterion= 'entropy', max_depth= 5,max_features= 'log2',n_estimators= 10),
    AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators= 300),
    SVC(kernel = 'rbf',C=1,gamma='auto'),
    MLPClassifier(alpha=1)
   
]

models = zip(names, classifiers)

In [28]:
scoring='accuracy'

results = []
names = []

for name, model in models:
    kfold = model_selection.KFold(n_splits=10, random_state = None)
    cv_results = model_selection.cross_val_score(model, X_train, y_train, cv=kfold, scoring=scoring)
    results.append(cv_results)
    names.append(name)
    msg = "%s: %f " % (name, cv_results.mean())
    print(msg)

scores = []

for model_name, mp in model_params.items():
    clf =  GridSearchCV(mp['model'], mp['params'], cv=10, return_train_score=False)
    clf.fit(X_train,y_train )
    scores.append({
        'model': model_name,
        'best_score': clf.best_score_,
        'best_params': clf.best_params_
        
    })
    
df = pd.DataFrame(scores,columns=['model','best_score','best_params'])
